The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Worlds top shuttlers in fray
                                                   Worlds top shuttlers in fray
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi : Top shuttlers from all over the world will take part in the Yonex Sunrise Indian Open to be held in Hyderabad from April 1 to 6.         
	Addressing a press conference on Friday, Badminton Association of India (BAI) president V.K. Verma said the $120,000 tournament will feature three of the top 10 men players and six of the top 10 women players.         
	Top international players like womens world No. 1 Xie Xing Sang, No. 2 Zhang Ning and No. 3 Zhu Lin are taking part, Verma said.         
	This will an annual event from this year and would be rotated between different centres in the country, he added.         
	The Grand Prix may be elevated to the level of a Super Series event in the next two years, making it part of the most elite badminton circuit in the world.         
	Out of the 230 players from 27 countries taking part in the Grand Prix, 36 are Indians.                                                                                                                       
